article.headline: Houston 74, UTEP 67
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Robert McKiver and Marcus Malone each scored 19 points, and Houston clinched the third seed in the Conference USA tournament with a 74-67 win over UTEP on Saturday night. Malone and McKiver combined to make eight 3-pointers for Houston (16-4, 10-6), which won its seventh straight at home and avenged a road loss to the Miners earlier this season. Stefon Jackson led UTEP (15-15, 6-9) with 25 points and Victor Ramalho had 10 rebounds. Jackson was 10-of-14 from the floor, but his teammates combined to shoot just 27 percent from the field. Jahmar Thorpe added 14 points for the Cougars, who set a school record for Conference USA wins in a season. The Miners, who are 2-9 in their 11 games, will be the No. 10 seed in the conference tournament.
